import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['wounds'], label='Wounds')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['other'], label='Other Injuries')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['disease'], label='Disease')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the trend of wounds, other injuries, and disease over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['wounds'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Wounded Soldiers')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wounds?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
